### Portfolio Backend API Tests
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension

### 1. Test server is running
GET http://localhost:5000

###

### 2. Register a new ADMIN user
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "admin123",
  "name": "Admin User",
  "role": "admin"
}

###

### 3. Register a GUEST user
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "guest@example.com",
  "password": "guest123",
  "name": "Guest User",
  "role": "guest"
}

###

### 4. Login as ADMIN (copy the token from response)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

###

### 5. Login as GUEST (copy the token from response)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "guest@example.com",
  "password": "guest123"
}

###

### 6. Access Dashboard (Protected Route) - Replace YOUR_TOKEN
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

###

### 7. Get all projects (Public - no auth required)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/projects

###

### 8. Create a new project (ADMIN ONLY - Replace YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/projects
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "E-Commerce Platform",
  "description": "Full-stack e-commerce application with shopping cart and payment integration",
  "technologies": ["React", "Node.js", "Express", "MongoDB", "Stripe"],
  "image": "https://via.placeholder.com/400x300",
  "link": "https://example.com",
  "github": "https://github.com/username/ecommerce"
}

###

### 9. Try to create project as GUEST (should fail)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/projects
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_GUEST_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Should Fail",
  "description": "This should not work for guest users"
}

###

### 10. Try to access dashboard without token (should fail)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/dashboard

###

